title.narrative: Contracts to Hunger Safety Net Programme Implementing Partners

description.narrative: This activity (Contracts to Hunger Safety Net Programme Implementing Partners) is a component of Kenya Social Protection Programme reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £9,793,523. This component benefits Kenya, and works in the following sector(s): Social Protection. , with the following implementing partners: Coffey International Development, DAI Europe, Development Pathways, HelpAge International, Mokoro ltd., Mott MacDonald Limited, Oxfam GB, Oxford Policy Management. The start date is 26-07-2007 and the end date is 26-07-2017.
